Moodify is a clean, responsive UI for a mood-based music player app. The interface allows users to select their mood (e.g., Happy, Sad, Energetic, Calm) and receive playlist suggestions accordingly. The project focuses purely on frontend designâ€”no backend or API integrationâ€”making it ideal for beginners. It features animated buttons, color-changing backgrounds based on mood, and a modern card layout for playlists. Moodify demonstrates essential UI/UX concepts like user interaction feedback, responsive layout, smooth transitions, and color psychology in design.


